LITTLE ROCK, Ark. (KTHV) – Well, Week 8 of high school football action is in the books! A lot of teams had to deal with their first rainy games in a while as wet weather made its way through the state. However, that didn’t stop teams from scoring early and scoring often. A couple of upsets this week made it one of the most memorable of the season so far as we approach playoff time. Take a look at some of our highlighted games below: 
McClellan 44, Sylvan Hills 32 McClellan gets road win over Sylvan Hills KTHV 
Clarksville 21, LR Christian 58 LR Christian rolls over Clarksville KTHV 
Clinton 20, Baptist Prep 27 Baptist Prep beats Clinton 27-20 KTHV 
Mountain Home 21, Cabot 62 Cabot moves to 8-0 with win over Mountain Home KTHV 
Lake Hamilton 9, Benton 31 Benton beats Lake Hamilton 31-9 KTHV 
Van Buren 0, Bryant 30 Bryant dominates Van Buren 30-0 KTHV 
Conway 28, LR Catholic 10 Conway beats Catholic 28-10 KTHV 
Mills 7, Pulaksi Academy 60 Pulaski Academy picks up road win over Mills KTHV 
Har-Ber 38, Southside 0
